  "prompt": "Do guys friendzone you because they dont want to lose you?",
  "response": "The friendzone is a complex and often misunderstood concept. Sometimes, a guy might place someone in the friendzone because he genuinely values the person as a friend and wants to keep that relationship intact without risking it by pursuing a romantic connection. He might fear that a romantic relationship could complicate things or lead to losing the friendship if things don\u2019t work out.\n\nHowever, it\u2019s important to remember that people\u2019s motivations vary greatly. Not everyone views relationships or friendships in the same way, and being friendzoned doesn\u2019t always mean someone is worried about losing you. It could simply mean they don\u2019t feel a romantic connection or aren\u2019t ready for a relationship.\n\nUltimately, communication is key. If you feel confused about someone\u2019s intentions, having an honest conversation can help clarify where you both stand.",
